CatDescriptText: Mr. Willie Jones, 13 Reed Street, was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 29, 1958, pg.2 with question: "Do people, whom you know, place more emphasis on social life than civic responsibilities?" answer reads: "Most of the persons are interested in having a good time."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Willie Jones, wearing dark striped pants, dark suede zippered jacket, and multicolor plaid cap, holding paper bag under arm, standing on Liberty Avenue in front of Jenkins Arcade
